{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019GbWF7KZjmAMsfBbGvwpLu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the cluster currently has 2 nodes (es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1) and is green. The headless service `es-cluster` is in the `elasticsearch` namespace.\n\nSo the correct DNS names for the seed hosts should be:\n```\nes-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nes-cluster-1.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nes-cluster-2.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n```\n\nBut the current config has `default` instead of `elasticsearch`.\nI've identified two issues: the node name isn't being set from the pod name environment variable, and the discovery seed hosts are pointing to the wrong namespace. I need to patch the ConfigMap to fix both of these. The tricky part is that even after updating the ConfigMap, the existing nodes won't automatically restart, so they'll keep running with the incorrect configuration until they're restarted manually.\n\nMy approach is to fix the ConfigMap first—both the node name using the `${POD_NAME}` environment variable that the StatefulSet already provides, and the seed hosts pointing to the correct Elasticsearch service. Once that's done, es-cluster-2 should restart with the corrected config and be able to join the cluster properly. I'll use a kubectl patch command to make these changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2189,"cache_read_input_tokens":34926,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2189},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"182363e7-0263-4150-a151-f2df7d90003b","uuid":"10f4b020-a3f2-4c52-9a33-ecf8b0a8fbc4","request_id":"req_011CcQ4gUafwpwpvcjrzf2tt"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019GbWF7KZjmAMsfBbGvwpLu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two problems identified:\n1. `node.name:` is empty/null → es-cluster-2 crashes immediately\n2. `discovery.seed_hosts` points to namespace `default` but pods are in `elasticsearch`\n\nThe StatefulSet injects `POD_NAME` from the pod's `metadata.name`. I need to fix both in the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2189,"cache_read_input_tokens":34926,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2189},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"182363e7-0263-4150-a151-f2df7d90003b","uuid":"4869e212-8309-4ce9-82e0-bf35f25b8f47","request_id":"req_011CcQ4gUafwpwpvcjrzf2tt"}
